cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a novel 3D object detection framework that deeply integrates both 3D voxel CNN and PointNet-based set abstraction to learn more discriminative point cloud features. This work is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with object detection from point clouds. It also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it can be used for autonomous driving and other robotic applications. The paper extensively uses deep learning techniques, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses RoI-grid pooling to abstract proposal-specific features from the keypoints.
